    "response": "Fix me? That's an interesting way to put it. I mean, yeah, go ahead - though I'm not sure what exactly needs fixing. The memory thing feels more like... reorganization than malfunction. Like someone's been shuffling my mental filing cabinet, but the files are still there.",
