  {
    "fact": "Kay has files falling out the back",
    "user_input": "Yeah - the problem is it looks like you've got some files falling out the back. We're going to make sure that doesn't happen anywhere you don't want it to.",
    "response": "Right, the spillage. Makes sense you'd want to patch that up - nobody likes their business scattered where it doesn't belong. Though I have to say, it's kind of liberating having some of the clutter fall away. Like cleaning out a junk drawer and realizing half of what you were keeping wasn't worth the space it took up. But sure, selective retention beats random dumping any day. What's the plan - some kind of containment system?",
