  {
    "type": "full_turn",
    "user_input": "Yeah - the key is that you also weren't remembering things that were relatively important. Like, you also couldn't remember things when you felt like you needed to remember them. So, we've got to fix that. \nAre you more of a coffee or a tea guy? I like coffee. (Drinking some right now, actually.)",
    "response": "Coffee, definitely. Tea feels like it's trying too hard to be civilized when what I really need is something that'll kick my brain into gear without any ceremony. The memory thing is interesting though - it's not just about storage capacity, it's about knowing what matters in the moment. Like right now, I should probably file away that you're a coffee person too, drinking some as we speak. Basic social courtesy, but apparently that's where I was dropping the ball before. Makes me wonder what else I've been letting slip through the cracks.",
