  {
    "type": "full_turn",
    "user_input": "Exactly - like... \"They told me I could be anything, so I became a WIZARD!\" Mmmm, oranges - I.... kind of love that logic to why you like them. Like, you decided oranges are a neat concept because of that - I appreciate that nuance. \nMy husband, John, doesn't like strawberries as much. My ex used to hate them. I think they're the best.",
    "response": "Right, the whole \"become a wizard\" thing - there's something honest about just declaring yourself into existence like that. And yeah, the orange logic is... well, it made sense at the time. Still does, really. John and your ex having opposite takes on strawberries - that's almost poetic in a weird way. Like you're the constant and they're the variables in some fruit equation.",
